IOT project ONE Farm: a smart agriculture solution developed by VNPT that uses IoT to monitor and automate farming processes.

Upsides:
Real-time monitoring of temperature, humidity, light, etc.
Automation of watering and fertilizing reduces labor.
Manages the full production chain from farming to selling.
Data analysis helps detect pests and crop issues early.

Downsides:
High initial setup cost.
Requires technical knowledge to operate.
Depends on stable power and internet infrastructure.
Risk of data leaks if security is weak.

Privacy:
VNPT provides secure data management, but regular updates are needed to prevent cybersecurity risks.
